      "writtenOn": "2016-05-10T18:38:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is this test really meaningful here? It seems that all we\u0027ve done is create a test that will fail every 1/(2^64)th time. Obviously this is extremely unlikely but I\u0027m not a fan of trusting in luck. And it doesn\u0027t seem like a failure to generate that sequence of bytes anyway, at least not in the general case.\n\nIf we want to avoid this for the purpose of auth tokens wouldn\u0027t it make more sense to check for that situation in the token generation code and then have a unit test for that that has a seed for the RNG that is guaranteed to generate this sequence or a fake RNG that returns all zeroes the first time?",
